..., The problem was that HiveServer2 conf file had authentication = NOSASL, but the client was not prepared for this situation. Workaround is to add ";auth=noSasl" to JDBC URL.
I would say it's definitely a bug (at protocol specification level I am afraid, needs some re-design), and at least needs to be documentation., This workaround doesn't work with authentication set to CUSTOM.  Client still hangs., Any thoughts on this being a known JDK issue?
